refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public boolReflectionProperty::isDefault
Checks whether the property was declared at compile-time, or whether the property was dynamically declared at run-time.

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 &true; if the property was declared at compile-time, or &false; if
 it was created at run-time.

  &reftitle.examples;



    ReflectionProperty::isDefault example


<?php

#[\AllowDynamicProperties]
class Foo {
    public $bar;
}

$o = new Foo();
$o->bar = 42;
$o->baz = 42;

$ro = new ReflectionObject($o);
var_dump($ro->getProperty('bar')->isDefault());
var_dump($ro->getProperty('baz')->isDefault());
?>


    &example.outputs;


bool(true)
bool(false)
